27... Qg6 28. Rc1 fxe3 29. Nxe3 Bd7 $1 30. Rc7 (30. Rc4 Rf8) 30... Bg5 31. Ng4
Bxg4 32. Rxg7+ Kxg7 33. Bxg5 Bxe2 34. Qb3 (34. Qc1 Bf3 $1 {- this is not
possible with the rook on b8}) 34... Qxg5 $1 35. Qxb7+ Kh6 36. Qxa8 Qe3 $1 {,
spectacularly forcing a draw.}))) 21... Nh4 {(3)} 22. Qd1 {Now Yuferov is
