axb5 33. Na3 {(a5)} Rxc3+ 34. Bxc3 Qh4 35. Rg1 Qh3+ 36. Ke2 Kf8 {with equality}
) ({, and therefore it is better to play} 31. Be1 $1 {(defending the h4-square
and vacating d2)} b5 32. axb5 axb5 33. Nd2 Rxc1 34. Rxc1 Qg5 (34... Kf7 35. Ke2
$1 {and Nh2-f3}) 35. Bf2 {and Rg1, with the hope of successfully regrouping
