31. Rc3 $2 {Mistakes come in pairs...} (31. Be1 $2 {is also hopeless in view of
} f3+ $1 32. Nxf3 Qxe4 33. Ncd2 Qe2+ 34. Kh1 ({or} 34. Kg3 Re8 {etc}) 34...
Rxc1 35. Rxc1 e4 {(Crouch)}) (31. Ra3 $2 Qh7) ({but the tension would have
been retained by} 31. Ba5 $1 f3+ 32. Nxf3 Qxe4 33. Ncd2 {, although after} Qg4+
$1 34. Kf2 Rxc1 35. Rxc1 Qxa4 {Black's chances are clearly better.}) 31... Rc7
$1 {(8) The decisive manoeuvre: a mating attack on the g-file is threatened.}
32. Rg1 {A sad necessity.} ({If} 32. Kh1 Rg7 33. Rf3 {, then} Qg5 34. Rf2 Qg3
35. Raf1 Qd3 {and wins (Stohl).}) 32... Rg7+ 33. Kh1 Rxg1+ 34. Kxg1 Qh7 $1 {It
would appear that this 'long' queen move, emphasising the undefended state of
