Qf4 {(5) Audaciously leaving the bishop on g5 (from where it can no longer
retreat!).} ({What told was childish euphoria after my previous day's win over
Yuferov - absolute recklessness...} 20. Bh4 $1 {(Stohl)} Be6 21. Ng3 Rg4 22.
Re4 $1 {was better, with a clear advantage: by exchanging a pair of rooks
White relieves the pressure on g2, whereas the f6- and h5-pawns are
