boats behind him - the bishop will have nowhere to go. But what happens next?'
(Botvinnik).} ({The no less garish} 21. Qe5 $5 {also came into consideration -
but after} Bd5 (21... Qd5 $2 22. Bxf6 $1) 22. h4 $1 Kg7 $1 23. Qxd4 Kh7 {Black
somehow holds on.}) ({Therefore the strongest was} 21. g3 $1 {, killing the
counterplay on the g-file and retaining a loophole for the bishop at h4 
(although here White's advantage is not so obvious as after 20 Bh4!).}) 21...
Bd5 ({Moving the bishop out of range (} 21... Kg7 $2 22. Nxf6 {).} ({'Black
