h5 {(a variation by Stohl) is highly dubious, since Black does not have the
resource} Rxg5 $2 26. Qxg5 Rg7 {on account of} 27. Rxe7+ $1 Qxe7 28. Qxg7+ Kxg7
29. Nf5+ {and Nxe7}) ({but on the other hand} 24... Rh8 $1 {is quite suitable
- if now} 25. h5 {, then} Rxg5 $1 26. Qxg5 Rg8 27. Qh4 Bd6 28. Rf4 Bxf4 29.
Qxf4 Qd7 {with equality}) 25. Qxf6+ $1 Rxf6 26. Nxh5 Bh2+ $1 27. Kxh2 Qb8+ 28.
Nf4 Rf5 {is unclear.}) 23. gxh5 {(2)} fxg5 24. Qe5+ Kh6 (24... Rf6 25. Nxf6
Bxf6 26. h6+ $1 {.}) 25. hxg6 gxh4 26. Rf5 $1 {The most accurate solution.}
Kxg6 {This leads to instant death;} ({but Black would not have saved the game
with} 26... Rxg6+ 27. Kh2 {(f2)}) ({or} 26... Bxe4 27. Rxe4 Rxg6+ 28. Kh2 Bf6
29. Rxh4+ $1 Kg7 30. Rxf6 Qxf6 31. Qc7+ {, picking up with checks the pawns on
