- he attacked the annoying rook. But now White can advantageously regain the
material.}) 26. d8=Q $3 {(2) This move shocked Pribyl: the pride of White's
position - his passed d-pawn - sacrifices itself! 'A completely unexpected
idea of amazing beauty!' (Nikitin).} Bxd8 (26... Rxd8 27. Rxd8+ Bxd8 {loses to}
28. Qf7 ({or} 28. Rd1 $1 Qc8 29. Qf7 {(Nikitin)}) 28... Qd5 {(otherwise mate)}
29. Qxd5 Nxd5 30. Rd1 {.}) 27. Qc3+ $1 Kg8 28. Rd7 $1 Bf6 29. Qc4+ {'A very
important check;} ({if} 29. Qg3 $4 {there would have followed} Qe4 $1 {, when
Black wins.' (Pribyl)}) 29... Kh8 30. Qf4 $1 {The tempo play has concluded -
White wins the knight and remains with the exchange for a pawn and a solid
