} 9... O-O {White has the additional resource} 10. Qc2 ({while} 10. e4 Nxc3 11.
bxc3 c5 12. O-O cxd4 (12... h6 $2 13. Bf4 {, Kasparov-Marjanovic, Banja Luka
1979; Game No.100 in 'Revolution in the 70s'}) 13. cxd4 Nc6 14. Be3 Rc8 {
transposes into the main line (cf. the note to Black's 10th move).})) ({But
the most radical solution to Black's opening problems is} 9... c5 $5 10. Nxd5
exd5 {with a solid enough position.} ({Even} 10... Qxd5 {, a move criticised
by theory, is acceptable (Petrosian-Smyslov, 28th USSR Championship, Moscow
