11. dxc5 bxc5 {(Karpov-Najdorf, Mar del Plata 1982; Kasparov-Karpov, Zurich 
(blitz) 2006). This deprives White of a traditional trump - his mobile pawn
centre, although each of the captures on d5 has some drawbacks, and 9...c5 has
not had many supporters.})) 10. bxc3 Nd7 (10... c5 {is more energetic:} 11. O-O
Nc6 $1 (11... O-O 12. Qc2 {- Game No.52}) 12. e4 (12. Bb2 $5 {- Game No.85})
12... O-O 13. Be3 cxd4 14. cxd4 Rc8 15. Ra2 $6 (15. Qe2 {- Kasparov-Najdorf,
