{(4)} (12... O-O {is more accurate, maintaining the tension in the centre at
least until White determines the position of his queen's bishop. After} 13. Qe2
(13. d5 $6 exd5 14. exd5 c4 $1 15. Bxc4 Nf6 {, picking up the passed d-pawn})
13... Qc7 14. Bb2 {a fashionable tabiya arises (a joint one with the 7 Qc2
variation), where Black has tried} Rac8 {(Kasparov-Kramnik, Linares 2004),} (
14... Rfe8 {(Agrest-Akesson, Sweden 2006)}) (14... Rfd8 {(Ponomariov-Leko,
