4th game of their match in Merano), for example:} c6 (19... Qf5 20. Qxf5 Nxf5
21. g4 $1) 20. c4 Qf5 ({but} 20... Ng6 21. Bg3 Bc7 22. Bxc7 Qxc7 23. g3 Qd7 {
and ... Re8 is more consistent, gradually equalising}) 21. Qe3 $1 {.}) 19. Nd2
$1 {(4)} Be7 {(12)} ({Black evidently did not fancy the endgame with doubled
