should have played} 27. c4 $1 {and advanced his c- and d-pawns (not the a- and
b-pawns).} -- ({. The creation of a strong passed pawn would have placed Black
on the verge of defeat, for example:} 27... b6 28. g3 Nf7 29. Kg2 g6 30. Rc2 (
30. Qd5 $5) 30... f5 31. Qf4 $1 Qxf4 (31... Qc6+ 32. Qf3) 32. gxf4 Nd8 33. c5
bxc5 34. dxc5 Ne6 35. c6 $1 Bd6 36. Rd2 Bxf4 37. Rd7 {and wins}) ({, or} 27...
Nc6 {in the hope of} 28. Qe6+ ({but after} 28. Rd2 $1 {Black has a difficult
position -} b6 (28... Qb4 $6 29. Qd5+ Kh8 30. Re2) 29. a3 a5 30. Rd3 $1 {with
the threat of c4-c5, while if} Qd7 ({or} 30... Nd8 {, then} 31. Rb3 $1)) 28...
Qxe6 29. Rxe6 Kf7 $1 {.})) 27... g6 28. a4 ({After the belated} 28. Re4 Kg7 29.
c4 {there was the resource} b6 $1 {, when it is now difficult for White to
