I thought for a long time. At first it seemed to me that White's threats down
the h-file could easily be parried, and that the insecure position of the
white king would give Black good counter-chances. But on closer examination it
all turned out to be not so simple: the difficulties began to pile up one on
top of another, creating a veritable mountain of problems which was extremely
difficult to scale during the allotted time limit. I was quite unable to find
good squares for the development of my queenside pieces, and Black's position
ceased to appeal to me... --- I shouldn't have thought for so long over this
natural move!} (13... f5 $6 {(preventing f4-f5) would have led to a weakening
