approach does not always prove correct, as I came to realise within literally
a couple of moves.})) 33... Qe8 $1 {(3) From here the queen indirectly
defends the b5-pawn.} (33... Qd8 $2 {was much weaker in view of} 34. e4 $1 fxe4
(34... Nxb4 35. Rxb4 {and wins}) 35. Qxe4 {, when Black is lost:} Qe8 ({or} 
35... bxc4 36. Qxe6 N7b6 37. Rba3 $1 {also with a mating attack}) 36. Qxd5+ $1
