{with equality. Indeed, after} Qd6 14. Qe1 Bd7 {the game is roughly equal.}) ({
. However, it is more accurate to interpose} 12... Bg4 $1 {, and after} 13. Qe1
(13. Nf3 $2 Nh5 $1) 13... Nd7 $5 (13... dxe5 {is also not bad - now} 14. Nd5 $2
{is weak because of} h6 $1) 14. exd6 Ne5 {Black's unexpected activity more
than compensates for the sacrificed pawn.})) 12... h6 {(4)} 13. Nh3 {(21) Yes,
