23. Nd7+ $1 {is unclear because of 22...Qa4! (Crouch). --- Apparently in these
variations Gheorghiu was concerned about his restless king, but now Black goes
from the frying pan into the fire...})) 17. Bf4 $1 {This forces the opponent
to throw caution to the winds and bring his king into the centre of the board.}
(17. Bxd7+ $2 Qxd7 18. c4 $2 Be4 $1 {would have been too na’ve.}) 17... Qxf4 {
(13)} (17... Qb7 {was also hopeless:} 18. Bxd7+ Qxd7 19. c4 Qg4 20. Rxd5 Qxf4
