not obliged to lose, but after the approximate} 35... g5 36. Kxf2 Qc2 37. Kg3 (
{or} 37. Ne2 {he would also not have had any serious winning chances})) 36.
Ne4+ $1 {(disaster strikes from the other side)} (36. Bg5+ Kf5 37. Rf7+ Kg4 38.
Rf4+ Kh5 ({or} 38... Kg3 39. Ne2#) 39. Rh4#) 36... Kf5 37. Nxd6+ Kg4 38. Nh2+
