Qe7 21. Ne4 $1 Ne6 $1 (21... Bxf4 $2 22. Nf6+ $1) (21... dxe4 $2 22. Rd7) 22.
Nxg5 Nxg5 {was somewhat more tenacious, although in this case too after} 23.
Qg4 $1 (23. Bxg5 Qxg5 24. f4 {too is not bad}) 23... Ne6 24. Bh6 {White would
also retain a fearfully strong attack (} Kh8 $2 25. Qh5 $1 {). But now there
follows a decisive combination.}) 21. Ne4 $1 {(3)} Bxf4 {(7)} ({After} 21...
Be7 {my suggestion in 'The Test of Time'} 22. -- (22. Nd6 {(?!)} Bxd6 ({after
