1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 {(2)} 4. Nc3 c6 {(5)} 5. Bg5 dxc4 ({Naturally, I
had prepared for a repetition of our duel in the Interzonal Tournament (1982):
} 5... h6 6. Bh4 $5 ({not the insipid} 6. Bxf6) 6... dxc4 7. e4 g5 8. Bg3 b5 9.
Be2 Bb7 10. e5 $5 {a novelty;} ({later both} 10. Ne5) ({and} 10. h4 g4 11. Ne5
{were introduced}) 10... Nd5 11. h4 Qa5 (11... g4 $5) 12. Rc1 g4 13. Nd2 c5 $1
14. Nce4 $6 cxd4 15. O-O h5 $6 (15... Nc6 $1) 16. a4 $1 a6 $2 (16... d3 $1) 17.
b4 $2 ({and here instead of the senseless 17 b4 White had the very strong} 17.
