19. Nxc4 Nc3 20. Nxc3 dxc3 21. Nd6+ Bxd6 22. exd6 Qf6 23. Qd3 O-O 24. Rxc3 Bd5
$1 {(when Tal agreed to a draw!). --- But on this occasion Tal unexpectedly
chose the most critical line, by immediately capturing the c4-pawn.}) 6. e4 {
(2)} b5 7. e5 h6 8. Bh4 g5 9. Nxg5 hxg5 10. Bxg5 Nbd7 11. exf6 {(2)} Bb7 12. g3
c5 {(3)} 13. d5 Qb6 ({Black is following the main line of the Botvinnik
