O-O 9. Bg5 cxd4 10. Nxd4 h6 11. Bxf6 Bxf6 12. Nb3 d4 13. Ne4 Be7 14. Rc1 Qb6
15. Nec5 Rd8 16. Rc4 Bxc5 17. Nxc5 Qxb2 18. Qc2 Qxc2 19. Rxc2 Rb8 20. Rb2 Rd6
21. Rd1 b6 22. Nb3 Bb7 23. Rbd2 Rbd8 24. Kf1 Ba6 25. Bxc6 Rxc6 26. Nxd4 Rc5 27.
Nb3 {(2) Simplification always seems the most reliable way to draw;} ({but
the knight on d4 stood well, and therefore Petrosian's recommendation} 27. Ke1
{and e2-e3 was sensible.}) 27... Rxd2 28. Rxd2 Rc7 {(3)} 29. Rd8+ {(14) 
Driving the black king away from the centre;} ({although the immediate} 29. Ke1
