) 42. e3 Bxe3+ 43. Ke2 axb2 44. Rb1 {with a probable draw:} Bxd4 ({or} 44...
Bc1 45. Rb5 b3 46. d5+ (46. h5 f6 $1) 46... Ke5 47. Rb7 Kxd5 48. Rxf7 Re3+ 49.
Kd1 {etc.}) 45. Rxb2 Re3+ 46. Kd2 Rg3 47. Rb1 {.}) 41. exd3 {Here the game was
adjourned, and I sealed the obvious move.} Bxf4+ {After a detailed analysis it
